Maternus had occupied himself (0. 40) with an examination of the argu- ments of Secundus, which he had drawn from the political conditions of the Republic (0. 36-37 ext). Beginning with 0. 38, Secundus discussed the constitution of the law-courts. Accordingly Maternus, following the same order of topics‚ proceeds with a consideration oi the statements in this second part of Secundus' speech.
